task.summary: Default task
Added RGBA.
Added toArray method to RGBA. Added constructor for UnicodeResource that accepts a File.
Changed offset to long.
Added toArray method.
Fixed a bug in GraphicsConverter.
Working towards code generation support. Renamed Graph to Chart to avoid confusion with org.almostrealism.graph.Graph.
This is version 0.5.
Starting release candidate for version 0.6.
Some improvements to the code generation features.
Introduced PairFunction. Phasing out Vec2.
Introduced VectorFutureAdapter and VectorProduct.
Improved merge in Shell to avoid unmodifiable list.
Introduced AcceleratedFunctions and GPUOperator, as well as some other classes involved in maintaining a OpenCL program and the corresponding set of named functions therein.
This is version 0.6.
Beginning version 0.7.
Introduced Pipeline (combination of Juncture and Producer). Updated GraphicsConverter so that each column can optionally notify a Pipeline.
Improved RealizableImage so that evaluate returns rapidly with partial image data if the image pixel futures are not complete.
Added isComplete and getCompleted methods to RealizableImage.
Fixed a(n unbelievably challenging to diagnose) problem with hardware acceleration. Introduced hardware acceleration for TransformMatrix.
Corrected TransformMatrix.getMatrix method.
Implemented TransformMatrix.clone.
Fixed bug in kernel programs.
Release cl_mem in finalizer.
Store Ray in cl_mem. This is version 0.7.
Starting version 0.8.
Migrating towards use of Producer throughout algebra and geometry packages.
Added cl_khr_fp64 extension to local.cl.
Some improvements to transformAsLocation and transformAsOffset as well as the introduction of rayMatrixTransform method.
Matrix transform accelerated operations are no longer kernel'd.
Many matrix operations and vector normalize converted to accelerated producers.
Hardware acceleration for a range of other functions, as well as conversion of RGB to use cl_mem.
Many minor improvements in further migration to using Producer throughout the API. Introduced RGBMultiply.
Many improvements working toward using Producer in place of Scalar.
Added cast.
Work around for generics issue.
Corrected AbstractSurface constructor.
Improved error message when arguments to a HardwareOperator are null.
Introduced support for custom handling of null arguments by AcceleratedProducers. RayPointAt is the first to allow null values.
Corrected null handling in AcceleratedProducer.
Handle null in ShadableIntersection.
Added support for OpenCL operations stored alongside subclasses of AcceleratedProducer. Moved some functionality of Ray into local.cl.
Introduced RankedChoiceProducer, which selects a Producer from a collection of ProducerWithRank based on the best rank (closest to zero without being negative).
ProducerWithRank is a Producer.
ShadableIntersection uses ProducerWithRank so that RankedChoiceProducer can be used in ray tracing.
Improved ProducerWithRank to deal with subclasses that implement evaluation directly.
Fixed a bug with ProducerWithRank constructor.

Fixed a bug involving Plane intersection that resulted in the RayPointAt operation produced during intersection to be against the transformed ray rather than the original ray (this issue exists elsewhere and will have to be resolved). This required changing the function of RayMatrixTransform so that it uses a new operation, RayCopy, to avoid side-effecting the original ray. This pattern should be exported to other areas of the code, with the Copy operations eventually being hardware accelerated with OpenCL. This commit also includes a significant expansion of the test suite(s).
Introduced GeneratedOperatorMap, and a correspond test, to explore a way to generate OpenCL functions on the fly.
Basic implementation of getScope for HardwareOperator. This will likely move to AcceleratedProducer.
